Complaints about cold-calling telemarketing firms and spam text messages rose more than 40 per cent last year.

The latest figures reveal there were more than 7,000 complaints from the public to the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO) in 2011/12, up from fewer than 5,000 the previous year.

A Panorama investigation on Monday claimed that the Government-regulated service, the Telephone Preference Service, intended to allow people to block cold callers, was being ignored by some telemarketing firms.

